Blogging used to be my escape root to all unhappy thoughts, it also used to be my source of happiness where I&nbsp;drop by to read all the happy moments, precious thoughts and lovely memories. But as the days pass, I&nbsp;don't know what to put down to words.&nbsp;

It's like words can't capture the moment, it can't relive the state you've been in, and it definitely cannot bring you back to the point of time. Undeniably, it lets you save and remember the time.&nbsp;

Sometimes having too much to pen down is a chore, you don't know where to begin where to end and probably that's how I'm feeling now. Just know that I had a great time with my family to Europe. Got a Gucci bag that's about $1.2k. Had a carefree worry-less life there. Everyone's slow paced, they don't believe in over-time work at all, working hours you see cafes filled with people drinking leisurely, you see tons of people in boutiques like LV.&nbsp;

Then when you're back in Singapore, bam!&nbsp;Everything starts on the spot. All your worries, stress, confusion are all back. What to do, where to go, what route should you take, go for this job or that, reply them or not?&nbsp;Do the design work or not, quotation of package rate?&nbsp;Then you start to wonder if this is really what you want to do. You are new you haven't tried the industry you don't know how things go and you have to keep asking around to get your own final answer. How tiring. Replying emails, discussing, on-hold projects.&nbsp;

Isn't that the life of Singaporeans?&nbsp;Non-stop, on-the-go, all for what?&nbsp;Money?&nbsp;

Dear bb got his day off tomorrow from Barry just 'cus I'll be flying off!&nbsp;Awwwwww, I&nbsp;bet Barry knows that he needs this off cus even when bb's working it's like as if he's in NS or something! haha.&nbsp;

Just got back from bb's place with Sheng &amp;&nbsp;Hao after 2 movies - Chipmunks 2 &amp;&nbsp;Drag Me to Hell!&nbsp;What entertaining genres man. Bb made tang yuan for me 'cus I&nbsp;was having gastric. Yummmmm, tomorrow when I wake up, I promise to make that betty crocker potato scallop! Din manage to do so just now, so it'll be like a lil surprise 'treat' for him too. heh heh.&nbsp;

Ahhhh, I&nbsp;really need to get a job when I'm back in Sg. Like, seriously. Just got an email earlier on, from a potential company to be a junior graphic designer. Aye, opportunities man!!! I shouldn't miss it for the world, but then again it's saikang and naturally fresh graduates are saikang for experience before we climb up that tough lil ladder called 'career-building'. I think I'll go for it, but I&nbsp;just found out from their website it's at Toa Payoh industrial area!!!! Let's just hope they'll take me as just a part-time/freelancer 'cus I'm gona continue studying ):&nbsp;And if that's possible, hopefully&nbsp;it's a job I'll enjoy with good working company and good pay!!&nbsp;$$$$$&nbsp;

Oh well, I&nbsp;always have to start from somewhere and I can't always have it my way to be within my area.&nbsp;

Amsterdam, is a smoker's dream: an amusement park of &quot;coffee houses&quot; that serve high-grade hash and pot under the tolerant watch of the government and legal authorities. 

Soft drug enthusiasts from around the world have made the pilgrimage to this Marijuana Mecca, from which they return with testimonials about some of the most potent weed they have ever encountered. 

&quot;The best high I ever had was the last night I was in Amsterdam last year, when I smoked a bag of Northern Lights and some other stuff I don't even remember buying, and finished it all off with a slice of space cake,&quot; said a smoker calling himself Lawnmower. &quot;And then I floated away to a land of many colors.&quot; 

Carl Lavin, an American who spent his winter holiday in Amsterdam, claimed that &quot;the average bag of weed was as good or better than anything I have ever gotten here [in the U.S.]&quot; &quot;The first bag was purchased at a reggae-themed coffee shop,&quot; he said. &quot;It was 9.07 EUR for a bag that lasted longer than our trip. It was called K2, and is simply the best weed I ever had.&quot; He said he fired up just before eating Christmas dinner, expecting a major case of the munchies. &quot;I never got hungry with this stuff,&quot; Lavin said. &quot;I didn't even finish my first plate. This stuff was that good. It didn't make me hungry or sleepy. Just high. Damn high. Rocky Mountain high!&quot;

I'm starting to feel a sense of insecurity and worry from someone whom I will not disclose but haha, seriously it's been a fucking year so who gives a shit what either of us think \m/__\m/ woooooooo.&nbsp;

I&nbsp;am gona be a good girl and do up one concept now, enough of complaining and thinking. I&nbsp;shall follow this motto&nbsp;&quot;Don't think just do!&quot;. And tomorrow will be a better day. No more Monday Blues but I'm going to school, ohhhhh fuck yeahhh huh. Take photos with all my other lovely graduated classmates, get my documents settled for application submission and apply for lasalle. Now, now, now. The thing about lasalle is that their degree courses are condensed with diploma courses. Seriously?&nbsp;That's from what I&nbsp;read, unless what I'm reading is wrong or I'm just ever so blur :]

Let's hope our portfolios are dope enough to go straight to level 3, or at least level 2. hoho.&nbsp;

&nbsp;Kina Grannis is ever so awesome. Yeah I do watch all her cover videos but if I&nbsp;hadn't watched what Amanda had posted, I&nbsp;think I'd only find out in another 2-3 weeks later. Funny how a single song can make your day, perk you up and get you on your feet. Her songs are all so good, but I love this one particular song. Morning blues are gone, and the only question is why am I smiling to myself when I listen to this song on replay over and over again.&nbsp;

Happy happy feelings. I'm imagining rainbows, cupcakes, picnic, sunshine, clear blue sky with patches of fluffy white marshmallow clouds, a field of cotton flowers, happy thoughts, happy people, happy couples. So happy that you can't even bear to tear.&nbsp;

I iz serenaded.&nbsp;

And for the record, just felt like saying this.&nbsp;

I love you my neighbour.
I love you my best friend's brother.
I&nbsp;love you my childhood friend.&nbsp;
I love you Fredick Wee.&nbsp;

There's no point in hiding anything.&nbsp;

I miss my boyfriend so much that every day I'd hope and look forward to a day whereby we can spend a whole 24-hour day together - doing retarded stuff, exercising, going out for a simple meal or movie. That's the whole cycle running through my mind everyday. I&nbsp;know I&nbsp;should be contented that I already get to see him every day. But I wanna do more than just putting him to sleep every night between like 1 - 3 am?&nbsp;

Every night, I&nbsp;watch him sleep, I hear him snore, I&nbsp;talk to him while he's already in dreamland, I&nbsp;notice all his little actions and funny moments, moments I cannot imagine how cute and irritating my boyfriend is when he's dead tired and mumbling nonsense away like literally.

What a workaholic you are but I still love you. I'm just getting a lil tired of waiting for your return every night. And if I'm out with my friends and you're home from work, I know you'd want me to be back, so of course I'd suggest that we all head home - motive?&nbsp;(almost last bus) but mainly,&nbsp;you. &nbsp;

Sadly I&nbsp;have no idea what to do with my one authentic pair of vintage heels which I&nbsp;bought for $89.00 from Granny's Day Out and only used it once. Shall I&nbsp;just throw it away?&nbsp;Who else would still want it right.&nbsp;

Anyway I&nbsp;have decided what I need and what I&nbsp;don't. All I need is.&nbsp;
1)&nbsp;A pair of wedges
2)&nbsp;A pair of black sandals
3)&nbsp;A pair of Dr Martens / New Balance
4)&nbsp;A pair of Vans shoes&nbsp;

That's just for shoes.&nbsp;
And where am I gona find the money?&nbsp;Good question,&nbsp;I&nbsp;still have to clear off all my debts first.&nbsp;

Sometimes&nbsp;I really wonder how people can ask me such stupid questions?&nbsp;It's the stupidest ever of all questions. Imagine how stupid and retarded the questions I can ask?&nbsp;Now imagine someone who's worse off.&nbsp;

It's like literally explaining everything already in a single sentence. Everything's stated there. And then you have one idiot asking you the exact same question which you have already explained (in hopes of not getting any questions again)&nbsp;

hello?&nbsp;What's in a quote and not quoted by me is a just quote. How can you break someone else's quote halfway right? Where are all the knowledgeable people out there, I thought everyone's smart enough to know.&nbsp;
